The music video for Life’s Blood is HERE! 🌙 Link in my bio!

This is my first ever music video and I really appreciated the opportunity to visually represent the meaning behind the music. Honored to have @john.hancock.music ‘s beautiful production on this song!🙏🏼 

The video was choreographed, directed, and entirely made possible by Kristin Nicolaisen @knetic_ (@2kris2)! Thank you for contributing your creative vision and your expertise throughout each step of the process; from envisioning the perfect choreography, to bringing everyone together, finding outfits, locations, and of course, being a beautiful dancer & teaching me to dance! ❤️ 

Shot, directed, and edited by Erick Yanez @erickyanezzz (EY Visuals @ey.visuals) who perfectly turned the vision into reality! 

Starring these gorgeous dancers - 
Melena Flores @melena.flo.612 & 
Zoe Vanosten @zoevanosten, who both ended up improv freestyling a good portion of the shots in the video! 🔥 

Plus, thank you House of Dance @houseofdanceco for sharing your studio!🙏🏼

.
#singersongwriter #musicvideo #musician #cinematography #dancers #dancevideo #altpop #indie #newmusic #videorelease #austintx #thisone #singer

Thank you so much to everyone who has streamed, shared, saved and added “Life’s Blood” to a playlist! ❤️ Your support is so appreciated! Here are a few of the stellar playlists I’m grateful to be included on + part of a lovely review by @wepluggoodmusic!

This song fits well into sad playlists, but it also expresses a more emotionally-layered reflection on the ephemeral and cyclical nature of life; both the sorrow & the beauty. 🦋

Happy October, everyone! 😻 I’m back with 1. a pumpkin painted with little cats dressed up in ghost costumes (this was probably the most important thing I did in the interim) and 2. an alternative lyric video for my last release.

Everything in the video is original footage I layered together (with the exception of the moon phase centerpiece, which is courtesy of NASA). 

Up on my YouTube channel! Link in bio. 

PS. John painted pumpkins with me (his pumpkin features the giant eye) & we had a grand time.

Dare I say it, I’ll be finishing my album this year!🤞 Here’s to a stellar 2024 for all of us! Cheers & love ❤️🥂
